===Usage===
* Traditionally in English, the proper noun ''Ukraine'' was used with the [[definite article]], ''[[the]]''.  However, this usage appears to become less common (see [[#References|References]]).
* In Russia, Украина is always used with the preposition [[на#Russian|на]], as in
:: {{RUchar|[[я#Russian|Я]] [[жить|живу́]] [[на#Russian|на]] Украи́не.}} — ''I live in Ukraine''.
: In Ukraine, Украина is nowadays mostly used with the preposition [[в#Russian|в]], as in
:: {{RUchar|[[я#Russian|Я]] [[жить|живу́]] [[в#Russian|в]] Украи́не.}} — ''I live in Ukraine''.
: The argument for the usage by Ukrainians is that “на Украине” implies Ukraine still being a part of [[Russia]] (or [[USSR]]), which Ukraine ceased to be in 1991.

* {{RUchar|Укра́ина}} is a common [[mispronunciation]].

